findings: Tessellation with valid spacing (dx=1.0, dy=1.1) produces score 0.605 for N=18
Baseline score for similar N is ~0.37 - tessellation is 63% WORSE
All tessellation configurations failed to beat baseline
The baseline uses sophisticated continuous angle optimization that tessellation cannot match
conclusion: Egortrushin tessellation approach produces WORSE scores than baseline. The baseline is at a very strong optimum that cannot be improved with grid-based approaches.
